📊 Project: Book Sales Analysis

I just completed an exploratory data analysis on a books sales dataset (1,000+ records), uncovering key patterns in pricing, author performance, and genre popularity.

🔍 Key Insights:
• Lower price points ($2–$8) drive the highest unit sales — clear price sensitivity
• "Excellent" rated authors generate ~10x higher median sales than other tiers
• Genre fiction dominates both in volume and rating count
• English-language books make up ~95% of the dataset

📈 Visualizations include:
• Box plots by genre & author rating
• Scatter plots: price vs. units sold, rating vs. popularity
• Time series of sales trends
• Top 10 authors by gross sales

💡 Business takeaway: Quality matters, but pricing strategy and author reputation play equally critical roles in driving sales.


